<Base
  title="Founder — Nous Ergon"
  description="Brian McMahon founded Nous Ergon, an applied AI lab, in March 2026 — after a career spanning investment banking and investment advisory, then eight years of data engineering and machine learning in fintech and healthcare."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-12">
    <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-zinc-100 mb-2">Brian McMahon</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500 mb-8">Founder</p>

    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      Brian founded Nous Ergon in March 2026 to build agentic systems against
      problems with measurable, continuously verifiable outcomes. The lab is
      the convergence of two careers &mdash; a decade in finance, then a decade
      in data and machine learning engineering.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">Finance</h2>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      Brian began his career as a CPA at Deloitte in Los Angeles, then spent
      four years in middle-market investment banking in San Francisco covering
      consumer companies, as analyst and associate. He moved to Asia, working
      in investment advisory before returning to the U.S. He holds an MBA in
      Finance from CEIBS and London Business School, and remains a CPA
      (inactive).
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">Technology</h2>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Back in the U.S., Brian moved into data science &mdash; earning an MS in
      Computer Science (machine learning specialization) from Georgia Tech and
      building over eight years across data engineering and data science in
      fintech and healthcare. On Change Healthcare's AI team, he owned
      production machine-learning systems for claim prediction at the largest
      U.S. medical claims processor. Most recently he spent four years at
      Block on go-to-market data engineering, where he owned the team's
      production data infrastructure end-to-end, led its dbt migration, and
      built multi-agent automation that cut per-pipeline migration time by
      over 90%.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm md:text-base text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      The lab's work is public and running:
      <a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="https://crucible.nousergon.ai/">Crucible</a>
      &mdash; the experiment harness for AI/ML research in live markets &mdash;
      publishes its results to a
      <a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="https://live.nousergon.ai/">live dashboard</a>,
      and the lab's
      <a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="https://dev.nousergon.ai/">developer tools</a>
      are open source on
      <a class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition" href="https://github.com/nousergon">GitHub</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-sky-400 mb-3">Links</h2>
